The article discusses the partnership between NATO and Afghanistan that was established at the 2010 NATO Summit in Lisbon. The leaders at the Chicago Summit reaffirmed this partnership and discussed further building the NATO-Afghanistan relationship. They agreed on the outlines of a new NATO mission to train, advise, and assist Afghan forces after the transition of security responsibility to the Afghans is completed by the end of 2014. The article also mentions the U.S.-Afghanistan Strategic Partnership Agreement signed by President Obama and President Karzai, as well as other partnership agreements signed by Afghanistan with various countries. The focus is not only on security but also on supporting Afghanistan's economic development. The international community aims to support Afghanistan in becoming less dependent on donor support and to increase economic opportunities.